== MM_FontSwitcher ==

--About--

	MM_FontSwitcher is a Gtk based Python script that can change the default fallback font of Ubuntu, especially 11.10, by clicking on the StatusIcon. This application is dedicated to the Ubuntu users who want to switch the system font easily between Zawgyi-One and Unicode standard font(used Tharlon for this applicaiton).


--Install--

1. Extract the downloaded Zip
2. Open the Terminal and change the directory into Extracted Folder
3. Type the command 'make'
4. Now you can find MM_FontSwitcher in Application list or Unity Dashboard Search

Note : To run the script on startup, you can use the script path "~/.mm_FontSwitcher/mm_FontSwitcher.py" for the Command in "Startup Applications".

--Uninstall--

1. Open the Terminal and change the directory into Extracted Folder(mm_FontSwitcher)
2. Type the command 'make uninstall'


